For Mongoose version 6+ (current) there is no more deprecation warning options, you can connect with the following:

Replace: mongoose.connect(uri, { useNewUrlParser: true, useCreateIndex: true });

With: mongoose.connect(uri);

This error is due to bootstrap. In your package.json, try adding these lines: 
for yarn:
"resolutions": {
    "autoprefixer": "10.4.5"
}
for npm:
"overrides": {
    "autoprefixer": "10.4.5"
}
Another method is to go to this path in your project ./node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css and search for the color-adjust:exact; and search for it (ctrl F) and replace it to print-color-adjust:exact;

