@Pal Sih You might wanna use npm concurrently. Super awesome package to run multiple commands at once.
Install that package, then just update your package.json scripts section to be like so:

"scripts": {
    ...
    "backend-install": "npm install --prefix backend",
    "backend": "npm run start --prefix backend",
    "dev": "concurrently \"npm run backend\" \"npm run start\""
  }

Also keep everything you have for backend inside "backend" folder inside root dir of your project. At the same level as your package.json file.

Last thing you need to do is just "npm dev" and boom, you have BE & FE running with just one command.

